of these to destroy stuff,

07:39.000 --> 07:40.835
but we make it to...

07:41.461 --> 07:43.421
Colors go in the sky,
and make "Oohs" and "Ahs."

07:43.546 --> 07:46.841
It’s called explosive entertainment,
where we're having explosives,

07:46.924 --> 07:49.177
but we’re here to entertain people
in a safe way.

07:50.428 --> 07:52.096
JEFF: <i>And yeah, you can’t help but notice</i>

07:52.180 --> 07:54.515
<i>that many of the world’s</i>
<i>most iconic displays,</i>

07:54.765 --> 07:58.102
<i>like Independence Day in the United</i>
<i>States, and France’s Bastille Day,</i>

07:58.186 --> 08:02.523
<i>and Guy Fawkes Night in the UK,</i>
<i>all commemorate violence.</i>

08:04.150 --> 08:07.737
<i>But apparently,</i>
<i>the spark behind all of this</i>

08:08.154 --> 08:12.116
<i>started with peace-loving monks in China.</i>
<i>How about that?</i>

08:12.950 --> 08:19.332
<i>The theory goes that back in 200 BC,</i>
<i>somebody threw some bamboo onto a flame,</i>

08:20.082 --> 08:24.295
<i>and thus something magical happened.</i>
<i>And that became a ritual</i>

08:24.378 --> 08:26.464
<i>that they thought</i>
<i>could banish evil spirits.</i>

08:26.631 --> 08:28.299
<i>Of course,</i>
<i>you know the history of mankind,</i>

08:28.424 --> 08:31.427
<i>this soon led</i>
<i>to the development of gun powder</i>

08:31.636 --> 08:34.889
<i>and the potential</i>
<i>for a great deal of harm.</i>

08:35.223 --> 08:36.599
<i>And so, it seems to me,</i>

08:36.682 --> 08:40.770
<i>that the story of fireworks is some kind</i>
<i>of strange marriage</i>

08:40.895 --> 08:42.730
<i>between obliteration...</i>

08:44.690 --> 08:46.692
<i>and prettiness.</i>

08:46.901 --> 08:49.737
(CROWD CHEERING)

08:50.613 --> 08:54.700
