JEFF: <i>Up, up, and away</i>

13:56.544 --> 13:58.337
<i>With the latest design software,</i>

13:58.420 --> 14:03.092
<i>one pilot is able to control the color,</i>
<i>and flight pattern of every single drone.</i>

14:03.175 --> 14:05.427
<i>-Geez.</i>
-PILOT: Be three minutes to launch,

14:05.511 --> 14:07.805
five minutes
and forty seconds to animation.

14:13.394 --> 14:14.436
PILOT: <i>Drones launching.</i>

14:14.520 --> 14:17.940
-(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)
-(WHIRRING)

14:18.357 --> 14:20.109
Oh, my gosh. Look at that!

14:23.696 --> 14:25.322
-They’re taking off.
-Yeah.

14:31.245 --> 14:32.288
Look at that!

14:32.413 --> 14:34.790
So, that’s three hundred
of them up in the sky.

14:35.040 --> 14:36.917
-That’s three hundred already?
-Right.

14:39.169 --> 14:40.504
-You've got to be kidding.
-(CHUCKLES)

14:41.255 --> 14:42.339
JEFF: You got to be kidding.

14:46.218 --> 14:48.262
-Whoa, that’s a jellyfish there.
-(CHUCKLES)

14:52.182 --> 14:56.228
Oh, my gosh. They’re becoming
something else. Wait a minute.

14:56.353 --> 14:57.730
I think I see…

14:59.315 --> 15:00.774
this is fantastic.

15:02.693 --> 15:04.987
White. Green. It’s the Earth.

15:05.070 --> 15:06.071
-It’s the Earth!
-Yes.

15:09.033 --> 15:15.289
It’s the globe spinning around.
Oh, my golly.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.711
<i>What a wonderful thing,</i>

15:21.712 --> 15:23.964
<i>and you feel some kind of power...</i>

15:27.676 --> 15:32.890
and some strange, indecipherable,
inconceivable intelligence.

15:33.891 --> 15:35.392
And it did put me in a state of...

15:36.310 --> 15:38.771
you know, wonderment and quiet...

15:40.522 --> 15:41.690
admiration.

15:43.525 --> 15:47.988
<i>And this feeling is different,</i>
<i>and I think we may have found our way</i>

15:48.072 --> 15:52.242
<i>into, not exactly pure fear or joy,</i>

15:52.326 --> 15:55.496
<i>but something profound, fundamental.</i>

15:57.289 --> 16:01.794
<i>Since the beginning of the species,</i>
<i>haven’t we looked up to the sky,</i>

16:01.919 --> 16:04.463
<i>for navigation and discovery,</i>

16:05.464 --> 16:09.635
<i>to learn about the universe</i>
<i>and our place in it?</i>

16:20.020 --> 16:23.816
Where in the heck are you taking me?
This is a place of darkness.

16:23.941 --> 16:28.946
I thought I’d take you to a place that is,
so far from really any ambient light.

16:29.029 --> 16:30.614
And the darker the sky...

16:31.448 --> 16:33.534
-The brighter the stars.
-JOHN: ...brighter the stars.

16:33.909 --> 16:36.036
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Liftoff on Space Shuttle Endeavor.</i>

16:36.245 --> 16:40.749
JEFF: <i>I am hitching a ride with the great</i>
<i>astronaut John Herrington.</i>

16:40.874 --> 16:42.042
FEMALE VOICE:
(OVER RADIO) <i>Go ahead, John.</i>

16:42.209 --> 16:43.419
JOHN: (OVER RADIO) <i>Houston, Endeavor</i>

16:43.627 --> 16:45.879
<i>-for EVA one and two.</i>
-JEFF: <i>And he...</i>

16:45.963 --> 16:50.968
<i>has had personal encounters</i>
<i>with the bright lights of connectivity</i>

16:51.093 --> 16:53.345
<i>that we have with the cosmos.</i>

16:53.762 --> 16:56.056
Well, the reality is that
if you look up at the stars...

16:56.181 --> 16:57.558
-Yeah.
-...and if you could imagine what

16:57.641 --> 17:01.520
a supernova looks like,
you can imagine what fireworks

17:02.229 --> 17:03.897
would be an image
for what you’d see in the sky.

17:04.023 --> 17:07.026
-Right.
-And tie that between what fireworks mean

17:07.109 --> 17:09.111
to us and what fireworks represent.

17:09.445 --> 17:11.321
-Yes.
- JOHN: So, let’s go see

17:11.405 --> 17:12.448
what’s really in the sky.

17:18.620 --> 17:20.289
-JEFF: Oh my gosh, I had no idea.

17:20.414 --> 17:21.957
-JEFF: This is dark.
-JOHN: Aw, jeez.

17:23.625 --> 17:25.169
-JEFF: Do you like fireworks?
-JOHN: Love fireworks.

17:25.252 --> 17:26.295
-JEFF: You do?
-JOHN: Sure.

17:26.378 --> 17:28.172
JEFF: Do they remind you
of the stars at all?

17:28.464 --> 17:30.466
JOHN: Well, you look up at the stars,
it looks like fireworks.

17:31.216 --> 17:32.259
I look up...

17:33.552 --> 17:35.304
Just the quietude, just the...

17:37.222 --> 17:41.518
What is that feeling?
Is there something in our consciousness?

17:41.602 --> 17:42.686
JOHN: So, imagine stepping out of the

17:42.770 --> 17:44.396
-space station, on a spacewalk.
-Yeah. Yes.

17:45.189 --> 17:46.899
JOHN: <i>I was hanging on the end</i>
<i>of the space station,</i>

17:47.149 --> 17:48.650
<i>-with a thumb and a forefinger...</i>
-JEFF:<i> Yeah.</i>

17:48.901 --> 17:50.235
<i>...looking out over the edge of the earth,</i>

17:50.402 --> 17:51.904
<i>-out of the vastest universe...</i>
-JEFF: <i>Yeah.</i>

17:51.987 --> 17:54.114
<i>...and the first time in my life,</i>
<i>I thought,</i>

17:54.448 --> 17:57.910
<i>"There’s nothing between me,</i>
<i>and whatever else is out there."</i>

17:58.911 --> 18:00.287
And what’s that...
How's that make you feel? Like...

18:00.370 --> 18:01.955
We were really, really, really tiny.

18:03.457 --> 18:05.959
It’s a sense of awe.
It’s a sense of, you know,

18:06.043 --> 18:08.962
appreciation for absolutely
how beautiful it is.

18:09.046 --> 18:12.132
You look at the stars and you think,
Whoa, gosh, well, how did they get there?

18:12.257 --> 18:14.510
It’s this idea that
what it makes you feel inside is

18:14.593 --> 18:16.804
an appreciation
for what you are a part of.

18:17.262 --> 18:19.681
This feeling of awe
that I get to be a part of this.

18:21.600 --> 18:25.938
JEFF:<i> Awe. Wow,</i>
<i>it's kind of a mysterious emotion.</i>

18:26.647 --> 18:30.692
<i>Intense pleasure,</i>
<i>seasoned with a sprinkling of fear.</i>

18:31.193 --> 18:34.530
<i>It can be set off</i>
<i>when we encounter a natural wonder...</i>

18:35.239 --> 18:36.365
(TRAIN ENGINE HISSES)

18:36.532 --> 18:41.120
<i>...or when we have an experience</i>
<i>that’s life-changing in some way,</i>

18:42.079 --> 18:43.789
<i>and when we see fireworks.</i>

18:44.164 --> 18:48.877
<i>You know, scientists say that if we can</i>
<i>appreciate our place in the universe,</i>

18:49.336 --> 18:52.464
<i>and become available</i>
<i>for that feeling of awe,</i>

18:53.215 --> 18:56.426
<i>it can generally make us happier,</i>
<i>and healthier,</i>

18:56.552 --> 18:59.847
<i>and give us some real humility.</i>

19:01.598 --> 19:06.061
<i>‘Cause it's an amazing thing, isn’t it?</i>
<i>That human beings, from the very start,</i>

19:06.145 --> 19:11.358
<i>looked up and were in wonderment</i>
<i>at what was around them.</i>

19:11.441 --> 19:15.070
I suppose lighting fireworks
is a kind of a

19:15.487 --> 19:19.074
naive, and sweet,
and primitive way of reminding us,

19:19.158 --> 19:22.619
and making a show
that is a little bit like

19:22.870 --> 19:26.248
the grand, natural, beautiful,

19:26.915 --> 19:29.918
<i>amazing show</i>
<i>that's in the sky all the time.</i>

19:30.043 --> 19:35.465
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

19:36.925 --> 19:40.220
JEFF: <i>Well, as this fireworks odyssey</i>
<i>of ours comes to a close...</i>

19:40.304 --> 19:42.139
<i>Hey, let’s check in with the Souza family,</i>

19:42.264 --> 19:44.474
<i>and see if they’ve put together</i>
<i>any kind of spectacle</i>

19:44.600 --> 19:47.519
<i>that may include me</i>
<i>banging on the pie-annie.</i>

19:49.646 --> 19:52.816
I brought the kids and Emilie,
and we’re about to,

19:52.900 --> 19:57.321
as the sun beautifully goes down
on this epic landscape,

19:57.446 --> 20:01.825
about to set off some fireworks.

20:01.992 --> 20:06.413
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

20:07.789 --> 20:09.124
JEFF: Okay, what am I looking at?

20:09.208 --> 20:11.293
Well, all right, so those are comets
that are gonna go like this

20:11.376 --> 20:12.586
-to the beat of the music.
-Oh, my...

20:12.753 --> 20:14.922
It’s going to go, you know, like a piano.

20:15.005 --> 20:18.634
We’re going to go,
one, three, five, seven. Two, four, six

20:18.717 --> 20:21.386
Back, back, back.
Yeah, exactly like a keyboard.

20:21.470 --> 20:23.931
Nobody has to run
in there and then do that?

20:24.014 --> 20:25.098
No, we don’t have to do that anymore.

20:25.224 --> 20:26.391
Where are you going to be?
Where am I going to be?

20:26.475 --> 20:27.976
I’m going to be with you.
We’re going to be out over here.

20:28.060 --> 20:30.270
We’ll all enjoy it just
as one happy family,

20:30.395 --> 20:33.023
in celebrating the fireworks.

20:33.148 --> 20:35.651
That’s what I was just saying,
celebrating fireworks, itself...

20:35.734 --> 20:37.861
Family, fun, entertainment.

20:38.779 --> 20:42.991
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

20:44.284 --> 20:46.328
-Is everybody ready?
-RIVER: Yes!

20:46.453 --> 20:50.415
-(ALL CHUCKLE)
-Okay, here goes.

20:50.499 --> 20:53.710
Thank you, Souzas, Charlie,
and River, and Emilie.

20:53.961 --> 20:55.087
Auto-fire! Here goes!

20:57.673 --> 21:03.095
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

21:16.316 --> 21:17.442
Wow! Look at that.

21:20.988 --> 21:25.701
JEFF: <i>I love the old-fashioned</i>
<i>artisanal craft of fireworks.</i>

21:25.826 --> 21:26.868
Oh, my gosh!

21:26.952 --> 21:30.497
<i>That real rawness of the sounds...</i>

21:31.164 --> 21:32.165
Wow!

21:37.504 --> 21:40.716
<i>...and those constellations of explosive,</i>

21:41.008 --> 21:43.510
<i>-gaudy, glittering jewels. I just love it.</i>
-Wow!

21:44.761 --> 21:46.388
-JEFF:<i> And nowadays...</i>
-Wow! Wow!

21:46.471 --> 21:51.059
<i>...it might not be the worst idea</i>
<i>in the world to get out,</i>

21:51.393 --> 21:57.316
<i>and experience that</i>
<i>fireworks anticipation and jubilation.</i>

22:00.610 --> 22:01.945
-RIVER: Wow.
-(CHUCKLES)

22:05.532 --> 22:08.243
JEFF: <i>Feeling ourselves</i>
<i>small in a big space</i>

22:08.577 --> 22:11.163
<i>gives us a sense</i>
<i>of connection to each other,</i>

22:11.246 --> 22:15.625
<i>and to this ample</i>
<i>and excruciatingly lovely planet.</i>

22:19.338 --> 22:22.758
-Oh, my god. It’s so beautiful.
-JEFF: Look at that. Look at it.

22:26.887 --> 22:28.472
JEFF: Wow! Wow!

22:29.598 --> 22:33.977
-(ALL CHUCKLE)
-JEFF: Oh, that was fantastic. Fantastic!

22:34.436 --> 22:38.940
It was a variety of sounds and...

22:39.107 --> 22:41.276
sights and light choreography.

22:41.360 --> 22:44.196
It was amazing, amazing, amazing.
Really wonderful.

22:44.529 --> 22:47.324
It gets ten Goldblums
out of a possible ten Goldblums.

22:47.407 --> 22:49.076
That's my highest possible rating.

22:49.618 --> 22:51.620
Amazing. Amazing.

22:51.703 --> 22:57.459
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

23:17.354 --> 23:21.483
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)
